words: and I uh secured a rank in the merit list. So in Indian schools we have uh, we do
not have high school in the same school. So basically at age sixteen we all kind
of graduate from our schools and uh then for two years we pick another high school.
So this uh exam which um marks the end of the school it's kind of a common exam
throughout the city and uh they also have uh
top twenty or twenty five people who rank in the merit list of the cities or the of
the exam. And uh I mean I always secured good grades, it's not like you know I was
a dumb child and this was certainly uh a great thing but, but still
it was um I mean there were many kids in my school who probably
were expected to uh secure a rank in the merit list and somehow none of them did and I surpassed

only one from my school so it was an even bigger deal. And that kind of uh
boosted my confidence and it was really something very positive for me because I felt um
for the first time that yeah I mean I knew I was intelligent but this kind of gave
me a push that yeah if I really decide to work on something I can be at the top.

proud because um I mean at, she had done everything single handedly and so
